fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Let
\alpha =(a_{1},…,a_{m})\in \Bbbk ^{m}
be such that \{a_{1},…,a_{m}\} is linearly independent over \Bbbk .

There exists a minimal linearly independent subset of these \alpha _{i}, and by relabeling (if necessary) we may assume they are \alpha _{1}, …, \alpha _{r}. Let
U:=\{(c_{1},…,c_{r})\in \Bbbk ^{r}\mid  c_{1}\alpha _{1}+…+c_{r}\alpha _{r}=0\}\subseteq \Bbbk ^{r}
be the subspace of coefficients for which the linear combinations of minimal independent subset of \alpha _{i} vanishes.
